      "content": "Originalism is a principle of constitutional interpretation that asserts the Constitution should be understood and applied as it was originally intended by the framers. Proponents argue that this approach maintains the rule of law, prevents judicial activism, and respects the democratic process by adhering to the text and historical context. Originalists believe that the framers' intent should guide the interpretation of the Constitution, ensuring stability and preventing judges from imposing their personal views. This method is seen as a way to preserve the Constitution's integrity and prevent arbitrary changes to its meaning over time.",
